[4] Sports-related superspreader events
[A1] Finland
Date: Tue 29 Jun 2021 04:31 JST
Source: NHK World [edited]
https://www3.nhk.or.jp/nhkworld/en/news/20210629_20/


Health authorities in Finland say about 300 people tested positive for the coronavirus after returning from Russia, where they watched matches of the UEFA European Football Championship. Finland played 2 group-stage matches in Saint Petersburg this month [June 2021].

Media reports say about 3000 Finnish supporters returned by bus after the 2nd match on 21 Jun 2021. About 800 of them reportedly did not go through virus testing, nor were asked to quarantine. The Finnish authorities are calling for all supporters returning from Saint Petersburg to take virus tests and isolate themselves until they test negative.

The Russian city is experiencing a rise in cases of the highly contagious Delta variant, first detected in India.

Soccer players and staff members are also found to have been infected with the virus at the South American football championship, known as Copa America, which is taking place in Brazil.

--
