Communicated by:
ProMED
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Data by country, area, or territory for 29 Jun 2021 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2021%20WHO%20Daily%20Tables%20JUNE29_1625078615.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 34.5% of daily case numbers and 41.4% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 72.07 million cases. Brazil reported over 33 000 cases over the last 24 hours, followed by Columbia (32 376), Argentina (12 105), and the USA (5558); 13 additional countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, while 4 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The European region reported 19.1% of daily case numbers and 15.6% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 55.83 million cases. Many countries not reporting cases in the last 24 hours or longer include Sweden, Belgium, Switzerland (2 cases), and Kazakhstan, among others; 6 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, and an additional 2 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 10.4% of daily case numbers and 7.6% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 10.94 million cases. Iran reported the highest number of cases (12 351) over the last 24 hours, followed by Iraq, Tunisia, Afghanistan, Oman, UAE, Kuwait, and Saudi Arabia. Pakistan and Jordan reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The African region reported 6.9% of daily case numbers and 6.8% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 4.01 million cases. South Africa (12 222) reported the highest number of cases over last 24 hours, followed by Namibia and Zambia. Zimbabwe, Rwanda, and Uganda reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases. Nigeria, Botswana, Gabon, and Congo, among others, did not report any new cases in the past 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 5.1% of daily case numbers and 3.4% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 3.53 million cases. Philippines reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours (over 5600 cases), followed by Malaysia, Mongolia, Japan, Cambodia, South Korea, and China.

- The South East Asia region reported 23.7% of the daily newly reported cases and 24.8% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 34.76 million cases. India is dominant, reporting over 37 000 cases, followed by Indonesia (20 467), Bangladesh (7666), Thailand (4662) and Myanmar (1312). Sri Lanka and Maldives did not report any cases in the last 24 hours.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 29 Jun 2021, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

